# Line-ending policy (coherent with .pre-commit-config.yaml and the
# validation hash design):
#   * Tracked text is normalized to LF — deterministic and cross-
#     platform. This includes the Fortran-format decks
#     (.bmi/.dat/.out) bundled under src/pybmodes/_examples/, so the
#     shipped samples are LF on every checkout.
#   * The gitignored upstream clones under external/ are untracked, so
#     these rules don't touch them — they keep their native upstream
#     line endings.
#   * Validation hashing is line-ending-normalized (CRLF -> LF), so
#     deck EOLs don't affect the integrity contract either way.
* text=auto
*.py text eol=lf
*.toml text eol=lf
*.md text eol=lf
*.bmi text eol=lf
*.dat text eol=lf
*.out text eol=lf
